data.chText: （陆军、海军陆战队或美国空军）上校
data.enText: an officer of high rank in the army, the marines , or the US air force

simple_means.memory_skill: colon + el 人；总称 → 上校

means: (陆军、海军陆战队或美国空军)上校

tr: a commissioned military officer in the United States Army or Air Force or Marines who ranks above a lieutenant colonel and below a brigadier general

value.def: A colonel is a senior officer in an army, air force, or the marines.

example.ex: This particular place was run by an ex-Army colonel.
example.tran: 这个地方以前由一位前陆军上校经管。

value.tran: (陆军、空军或海军陆战队的)上校
